   192	<task type="auto" tdd="true">
   193	  <name>Task 2: Emit the CentroidStream spectra_peaks facet for profile scans with label peaks</name>
   194	  <files>ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs</files>
   195	  <behavior>
   196	    - For an emitted spectrum where `scanEvent.ScanData == ScanDataType.Profile && scan.HasCentroidStream`, a SECOND read `ReadMZData(centroid:true)` returns the Thermo CentroidStream and those label peaks are written to spectra_peaks (same point struct, mz f64 / intensity f32, non-decreasing m/z, multiset preserved, same dense spectrum_index ordinal as spectra_data).
   197	    - A centroid-only scan (not Profile, or no CentroidStream) contributes ONLY to spectra_data — never duplicated into spectra_peaks.
