    45	---
    46	
    47	# Phase 2 Plan 01: Spectra Signal Data Summary
    48	
    49	**`-f mzpeak` now emits the full point-layout signal for every in-range spectrum under DUAL
    50	representation — `spectra_data` (as-acquired profile/centroid arrays) plus a conditional
    51	`spectra_peaks` facet (Thermo CentroidStream label peaks for profile scans that carry them) — with a
    52	per-ordinal `spectra_metadata` row set that covers the identical spectrum set, canonical widths
    53	(mz f64 / intensity f32), non-decreasing m/z with the multiset preserved, honored filters, and
    54	`sorting_rank:0` on `point.mz`.**
    55	
    56	## What Was Built
    57	
    58	- **spectra_data (Task 1):** Replaced the single-spectrum placeholder loop with a real per-scan loop
    59	  over `[firstScanNumber, lastScanNumber]`. Each scan gets its level via
    60	  `(int)raw.GetFilterForScanNumber(scanNumber).MSOrder`; scans with `level > MaxLevel` or
    61	  `!MsLevel.Contains(level)` are skipped (zero rows, not counted). For each emitted scan,
    62	  `ReadMZData(centroid:false)` yields the as-acquired arrays, which are appended to growing
    63	  `spectrum_index` (dense 0-based `ulong` ordinal), `mz` (f64), and `intensity` (f32) accumulators.
    64	- **spectra_metadata (Task 1):** `BuildMetadataFacet` now takes the collected per-ordinal lists and
    65	  writes one `spectrum` row per emitted ordinal (`index=ordinal`, `id="index={ordinal}"`,
    66	  `time=RetentionTimeFromScanNumber`). Its `spectrum_count` equals the `spectra_data` `spectrum_count`,
    67	  so the two facets cover the identical spectrum set.
    68	- **spectra_peaks (Task 2):** During the same loop, when
    69	  `scanEvent.ScanData == ScanDataType.Profile && Scan.FromFile(raw, scanNumber).HasCentroidStream`, a
    70	  SECOND `ReadMZData(centroid:true)` reads the Thermo CentroidStream label peaks into a parallel set of
    71	  accumulators keyed on the SAME ordinal. The facet is written (and listed in `mzpeak_index.json` with
    72	  `data_kind:"peaks"`) only when at least one peak row was accumulated. `BuildIndex(bool hasPeaks)`
    73	  gates the index entry.
    74	- **sorting + multiset:** `OrderedPairs` emits the Thermo-native ascending order and asserts
    75	  non-decreasing; only on a detected violation does it apply a stable paired index sort
    76	  (decorate-by-index, ties broken by original index). It never deduplicates or merges equal-m/z points.
    77	- **sorting_rank:** `SpectrumArrayIndex` now declares `"sorting_rank":0` on the `point.mz` entry.
    78	- **Tests (Task 3):** New `MzPeakWriterTests` (7 tests) lock ascending+multiset, f64/f32 leaf types,
    79	  MS2-only filter exclusion, metadata/data spectrum-set parity (dense 0..N-1), peaks `data_kind`
    80	  "peaks", and a non-tautological duplicate-m/z survival test driving `OrderedPairs` with
    81	  `{100.0,100.0,100.0,200.0}` (asserts 4 rows survive in input order).
    82	
    83	## Dual-Representation Routing (as implemented)
    84	
    85	| Scan kind | `spectra_data` (centroid:false) | `spectra_peaks` (centroid:true) |
    86	|-----------|---------------------------------|----------------------------------|
    87	| Profile + HasCentroidStream | as-acquired profile arrays | Thermo CentroidStream label peaks |
    88	| Profile, no CentroidStream | as-acquired profile arrays | — (not written) |
    89	| Centroid-only (ScanData != Profile) | the centroid SegmentedScan | — (never duplicated) |
    90	
    91	For `small.RAW`: 48 emitted spectra → 305,213 `spectra_data` points (matches the existing
    92	`TestParquetProfile` profile total) and 12,890 `spectra_peaks` points across the profile scans that
    93	carry a CentroidStream (well below the 48,520 centroid total in `TestParquetCentroid`, confirming
    94	centroid-only scans are not routed to peaks).
    95	
    96	## Verify-Gate Results
