   144	
   145	**Finding-list delta:**
   146	- `mz_monotonic_data` INFO — **RESOLVED** by declaring `sorting_rank:0` on `point.mz` (no longer
   147	  reported).
   148	- `columns_spectra_metadata` ERROR (`required facet 'scan' absent`) — **PERSISTS**. The per-ordinal
   149	  `spectrum` rows did NOT clear it: the validator requires the actual top-level `scan` facet
   150	  (`source_index`, `scan_index`, scan_start_time, filter_string, scan_windows, ...), which is
   151	  explicitly Phase-3 scope. Net result is one fewer finding than baseline; no NEW errors introduced.
   152	
   153	No gate was weakened to accommodate this — the persisting ERROR is the planned Phase-3 `scan`-facet
   154	item and is reported verbatim.
   155	
   156	## Deviations from Plan
   157	
   158	### Gate-command mechanics (no production/gate change)
   159	
   160	**1. [Rule 3 - Blocking] `dotnet build -c Release` from the git root has no project/solution to build**
   161	- **Found during:** Task 3 verify.
   162	- **Issue:** The verify command runs `dotnet build -c Release` with the repo root as cwd, but the
   163	  solution lives at `ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParser.sln`; MSBuild errored with
   164	  `MSB1003: Specify a project or solution file`.
   165	- **Fix:** Built the solution explicitly (`dotnet build -c Release ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParser.sln`)
   166	  and ran the test filter unchanged. The substantive intent (full build incl. tests, then run
   167	  `MzPeakWriterTests`) is met. No writer/test logic changed; same class of gate-command mechanics noted
   168	  in the Phase-1 SUMMARY.
   169	
   170	### Implementation choice
   171	
   172	**2. [Plan-permitted] `OrderedPairs` exposed `public static` rather than `internal`**
   173	- The plan allows extracting the emit step into "a small testable internal helper if needed". The test
   174	  project has no `InternalsVisibleTo`, so `internal` would not be visible; `public static` is the
   175	  least-invasive way to let Task-3 (f) drive the real emit path with deterministic duplicate-m/z input.
   176	  This adds one pure, side-effect-free helper to the public surface; no behavior change.
   177	
   178	**Total deviations:** 2 (1 gate-command path correction, 1 plan-permitted visibility choice).
   179	**Impact:** No scope creep, no production logic weakened, no gate weakened.
   180	
   181	## v1 Prototype Limitation (confirmed)
   182	
   183	v1 uses **full in-memory accumulation** of all point/peak/metadata arrays and writes a **single Parquet
   184	row group per facet**. No large-RAW-safe claim is made. Row-group batching (the existing
   185	`ParquetSpectrumWriter` flushes at ~1M rows so all ions of a scan stay in one group) is deferred as a
   186	**v2/OPT** follow-up.
   187	
   188	## What Phase 3 Needs
   189	
   190	- **The `scan` facet** (and `precursor` / `selected_ion`) in `spectra_metadata` — this is the one
   191	  remaining `mzpeak-validate` ERROR (`required facet 'scan' absent`). Phase 3 must add the top-level
   192	  `scan` struct (source_index/scan_index/scan_start_time/filter_string/scan_windows/...) referencing
   193	  back to the spectrum ordinals already emitted here.
   194	- **Rich `spectrum` metadata** beyond the honest index/id/time minimum: ms_level, polarity,
   195	  representation, lowest/highest observed mz, number_of_data_points, number_of_peaks, base peak,
   196	  TIC, parameters (use the `MzPeakParquet.BuildParamField` PARAM shape and the ground-truth
   197	  `spectrum_array_index` entries).
   198	- The dense 0-based ordinal contract (`spectrum_index`) and the per-ordinal metadata row set are the
   199	  join key Phase 3 should reference via `source_index`.
   200	- VER-02 facet equivalence vs mzML2mzPeak (profile-mode differential) remains Phase 4.
   201	
   202	## Self-Check: PASSED
   203	
   204	- Created file verified present: `ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakWriterTests.cs`
   205	- Modified file verified present: `ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs`
