   135	sample_list / cv_list per the schema/ JSONSchemas.
   136	
   137	## Implementation notes / risks
   138	- Parquet.Net v5.0.1 is already a TRFP dependency. The existing ParquetSpectrumWriter uses the
   139	  high-level `ParquetSerializer.SerializeAsync` over a *flat* struct. mzPeak needs **nested
   140	  structs + lists-of-structs + parallel nullable top-level columns** — likely requires the
   141	  low-level Parquet.Net schema/column API (`ParquetSchema`, `DataColumn`, struct/list fields),
   142	  not the POCO serializer. This is the primary technical risk → warrants an early spike.
   143	- `large_string`/`large_list` = Arrow large variants (64-bit offsets). Confirm Parquet.Net maps
   144	  plain string/list compatibly (readers likely accept both); verify with a round-trip read.
   145	- ZIP must be STORED (no deflate) at the archive level.

