   349	## Risks
   350	- **Value-merging / reorder silently loses points** (T-02-01) — mitigated by emitting Thermo-native
   351	  ascending order with an assertion (paired sort only on violation) plus the Task-3 multiset and
   352	  non-tautological duplicate-m/z assertions. No "stable sort preserves RAW tie order" claim is made; the
   353	  base `ReadMZData` order is taken as authoritative ascending.
   354	- **f64→f32 intensity narrowing is lossy** (T-02-02) — accepted as the declared canonical width;
   355	  Phase 4 records the transform for L2 tolerance.
   356	- **Memory blow-up on large RAW** (T-02-03) — ACCEPTED v1 limitation: full in-memory accumulation +
   357	  single row group per facet. Row-group batching is a v2/OPT follow-up; no large-RAW-safe claim is made.
   358	- **Dual-representation routing inferred from shape rather than availability flags** (T-02-04) —
   359	  mitigated by routing strictly on `scanEvent.ScanData==Profile && scan.HasCentroidStream`.
   360	- **Metadata/data spectrum-set drift** (T-02-05) — mitigated by per-ordinal metadata rows and Task-3 (d).
